On {{nihongo|June 21|6月21日|July 24, 939}}, it was reported that troops from {{ill|Mutsu Province|ja|Mutsu Province }} would be relocated. On {{nihongo|July 18|7月18日|August 19, 939}}, two additional decrees were sent to {{ill|Dewa Province|ja|出羽国}}. These instructed that weapons and armor stored in the provincial treasury be distributed to soldiers, that grain taxes be used as rations, that troops be trained to suppress the rebellion, and that {{ill|Akita Castle|ja|秋田城}} Governor {{ill|Minamoto no Yoshinari|ja|源嘉生}} be reprimanded.<ref>{{ill|Honchō Seiki|ja|本朝世紀}}</ref>
However, further historical records of the rebellion cease, and the subsequent course of the conflict remains unclear.
