== Events == On {{nihongo|April 17, Tengyō 2|天慶2nd year 4月17日|May 22, 939}}, a rebellion by the fushū occurred, engaging with the garrison at {{ill|Akita Castle|ja|秋田城|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Akita Castle|qq=}}. This event was reported to the {{ill|Capital of Heian-kyō|ja|平安京|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Capital of Heian-kyō|qq=}} as noted in historical records such as the {{ill|Nihon Kiryaku|ja|日本紀略|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nihon Kiryaku|qq=}}. On the following day, three imperial decrees were issued, instructing the training of elite soldiers, fortification of strategic locations, mobilization of vagrants regardless of status, and the ritual appeasement of {{ill|Ōmonoimi no Kami|ja|大物忌神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōmonoimi no Kami|qq=}}, as the oracle predicted that the {{ill|Mount Chōkai|ja|鳥海山|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mount Chōkai|qq=}} would burn. According to an excerpt from the {{ill|Teishinkōki|ja|貞信公記|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Teishinkōki|qq=}}, the rebels reached {{ill|Akita District|ja|秋田郡|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Akita District|qq=}}, plundering government rice stores. The same record mentions that the rebels were accompanied by "異類" (irui, "other kinds"), which various interpretations suggest might refer to other Emishi groups<ref>Akira Sekiguchi, 1992</ref>, the {{ill|Watari-shima|ja|渡島|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Watari-shima|qq=}} (ancestors of the Ainu)<ref>Ryōsuke Kumada, 2001</ref>, or even early {{ill|Ainu people|ja|アイヌ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ainu people|qq=}}.<ref>Takashi Takahashi, 1986</ref>
On {{nihongo|June 21|6月21日|July 24, 939}}, it was reported that troops from {{ill|Mutsu Province|1=Mutsu Province|2=ja|3=陸奥国|ja|Mutsu Province|1=Mutsu Province|2=ja|3=陸奥国|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mutsu Province|qq=}} would be relocated. On {{nihongo|July 18|7月18日|August 19, 939}}, two additional decrees were sent to {{ill|Dewa Province|ja|出羽国|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Dewa Province|qq=}}. These instructed that weapons and armor stored in the provincial treasury be distributed to soldiers, that grain taxes be used as rations, that troops be trained to suppress the rebellion, and that {{ill|Akita Castle|ja|秋田城|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Akita Castle|qq=}} Governor {{ill|Minamoto no Yoshinari|ja|源嘉生|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Minamoto no Yoshinari|qq=}} be reprimanded.<ref>{{ill|Honchō Seiki|ja|本朝世紀|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Honchō Seiki|qq=}}</ref>
However, further historical records of the rebellion cease, and the subsequent course of the conflict remains unclear.
